Author-Name:    Mayshar, Joram
Author-Name:  Yitzhaki, Shlomo
Title:   Dalton-Improving Indirect Tax Reform. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 793-807
Issue: 4
Volume: 85
Year: 1995
Month:  September 
Abstract:
  A tax reform is 'Dalton-improving' if it improves social welfare for all
 possible social-welfare functions that conform to Hugh Dalton's principle
 of transfers. According to this principle, there exists a prior social
 ranking of households and a transfer is approved if it it distributes from
 high-ranking ('rich') to low-ranking ('poor') households, without altering
 the ranking itself. In this paper, the authors develop a procedure for
 identifying marginal Dalton-improving reforms in the context of indirect
 taxation. The methodology is illustrated using data on excise taxes in the
 United Kingdom.   Copyright 1995 by American Economic Association.
