Template-Type: ReDIF-Article 1.0
Author-Name:    Perotti, Enrico C
Title:   Credible Privatization. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 847-59
Issue: 4
Volume: 85
Year: 1995
Month:  September 
Abstract:
  Privatization shifts residual income and control to private investors,
 restricting redistribution and improving incentives; thus rapid
 privatization should be desirable. Empirically, however, the transfer of
 ownership, as opposed to control, is very gradual. The author offers an
 explanation based on investors' concerns about future interference. A
 government averse to redistribution retains a passive stake in the firm;
 the willingness to bear residual risk signals commitment. When a large
 government stake conflicts with the transfer of control, underpricing may
 be necessary for separation. Finally, when the required discount is large,
 a committed government may prefer not to signal, gaining credibility over
 time.	 Copyright 1995 by American Economic Association.
