Author-Name:    Cogley, Timothy
Author-Name:  Nason, James M
Title:   Output Dynamics in Real-Business-Cycle Models. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 492-511
Issue: 3
Volume: 85
Year: 1995
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  The time-series literature reports two stylized facts about output
 dynamics in the United States: GNP growth is positively autocorrelated and
 GNP appears to have an important trend-reverting component. This paper
 investigates whether current real-business-cycle models are consistent
 with these stylized facts. Many real-business-cycle models have weak
 internal propagation mechanisms and must rely on external sources of
 dynamics to replicate both facts. Models that incorporate labor adjustment
 costs are partially successful. They endogenously generate positive
 autocorrelation in output growth but they need implausibly large
 transitory shocks to match the trend-reverting component in output.   Copyright 1995 by American Economic Association.
