Title:   Capital Structure and Product-Market Competition: Empirical Evidence from the Supermarket Industry. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 415-35
Issue: 3
Volume: 85
Year: 1995
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  This paper establishes an empirical link between firm capital structure
 and product-market competition using data from local supermarket
 competition. First, an event-study analysis of supermarket leveraged
 buyouts (LBOs) suggests that a LBO announcement increases the market value
 of the LBO chain's local rivals. Second, the author shows that supermarket
 chains were more likely to enter and expand in a local market if a large
 share of the incumbent firms in the local market undertook LBOs. The study
 suggests that leverage increases in the late 1980s led to softer
 product-market competition in this industry.   Copyright 1995 by American Economic Association.
