Author-Name:  Pines, David
Author-Name:  Thisse, Jacques-Francois
Title:   On the Optimal Structure of Local Governments. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 1224-40
Issue: 5
Volume: 85
Year: 1995
Month:  December 
Abstract:
  The authors show that space matters in designing the optimal provision of
 local public goods. Geography imposes a particular institutional structure
 of local governments due to the overlapping of market areas associated
 with different local public goods. The optimum can be decentralized
 through local governments that have jurisdiction over market areas of all
 local public good types. This implies that the appropriate suppliers of
 local public goods are metropolitan governments which finance them through
 user charges and land rent. In addition, the authors' approach invalidates
 the prevailing theory of fiscal federalism, according to which a layer of
 government should be established for each type of local public good.   Copyright 1995 by American Economic Association.
